---
By: Marcus Aurelius
Locus:
  Page: 105
  Verse: 16
Tags:
  - Discipline
---
The superior man is uncontaminated by pleasure, unharmed by pain, untouched
by any insult, feeling no wrong, not overpowered by passion, dyed deep with
justice, accepting with all his soul everything which is assigned to him as
his portion.
